# Copy to .env.local and fill from Supabase → Project Settings → API
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key

# Create an admin user in Supabase → Authentication → Users, then sign in at /admin.
# Run supabase/schema.sql in the SQL Editor once (table + Storage bucket + RLS).

# Vercel: add the same two variables under Project → Settings → Environment Variables.
# Enable them for Production (and Preview if you test preview deployments). Redeploy after saving.
#
# Vite inlines VITE_* at build time. If those are missing, the app also tries
# /api/supabase-config (serverless), which can read SUPABASE_URL / SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
# without the VITE_ prefix — but that route only exists on Vercel, not plain vite dev.
#
# Optional fallback names (also read at build time and by /api/supabase-config on Vercel):
# SUPABASE_URL=...
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=...
